<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-23T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-23T20:00:00-05:00" n="81" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1136</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-23T20:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">February
                                            23, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your February 21, 4 p.m., February 23, 4 p.m., and February 23, 5
                                p.m. The attitude of the American Government is stated in a telegram
                                of February 13, 7 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d81fn1">See footnote 1,
                                        <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_45">p.
                                        45</ref>.</note> to Tokyo which has already been repeated to
                                you. You will communicate orally to the Foreign Office the views
                                expressed therein.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>